"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Barcook Bakery does it well, and does it so so good. <br><br>There&#39;s always that long queue in the morning, so I try to avoid it and go in the afternoon instead, where the breakfast crowd has subsided and half the Raffles Place population have been chained to their screens. <br><br>I believe that the secret to their goodness lies in the fact that they are capable of getting such a great turnover rate at this location, which means that they can keep baking fresh goodies all day round, without them being left in the display to go stale. Which is why each bun you pick up is bound to be a little warm, a little crispy, and very good. I&#39;m a huge fan of their garlic bread, as long as you&#39;re not going for an interview after that. Well, it isn&#39;t that garlicky, just that I get fairly conscious about it. Otherwise the taste is great as it has that bit of cheesy crispy layer on it, and that much buttery goodness. <br><br>As a bakery, I&#39;m not sure how you get any better.",
