"reviewcomment":"Whenever friends tell me we&#39;ll eat at a Thai restaurant I always feel like declining. I know it will never be as satisfying as Nakhon. And so it is with my favorite Thai place in Singapore. I don&#39;t care that it&#39;s all the way in the East even though I live in the North.<br><br>My go-to dishes would be sweet and sour fish, beef green curry, basil chicken, kangkong sambal, and a nice steaming bowl of rice.<br><br>The mango sticky rice is a hit and miss but if I&#39;m craving one it&#39;ll do. Some days, particularly if I know I&#39;ll be having a spicy dish, I&#39;ll order Thai iced milk tea.<br><br>P.S. Sometimes it gets pretty noisy with the Thai heavy metal music. Still makes for a good laugh.",
