"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Rocher Original Beancurd is one of the best in Singapore. From $1 for a glass of beancurd drink to $3.80 for their XXL fried chicken, it&#39;s definitely an affordable dessert/snack place for you to pop by and chill with your friends. <br><br>However do take note to sit outside as inside can get quite stuffy sometimes. But then again, what you pay for ($1.80 for cold beancurd with pearls ) is what you get so no complaints there with the ambiance. Their beancurd are always a welcome dessert whenever I am in the area as it&#39;s silky smooth and sweet.. just the way I like it... the pearls is always something I like to throw in so I can chew on something. Seating always seems to be enough regardless of how crowded the shop looks.. I don&#39;t know how they do it but always there&#39;s enough space for everyone. Definitely an affordable and delicious place for you to go with your friends for a nice chat on Friday nights.",
