"reviewcomment":"Easily, among the greatest conjee experiences I have ever bad in my entire life.  Zhen Zhen is located inside the Maxwell Food Center.<br><br>Coming here seems like a religious experience because, why else would one wait in line on a Sunday morning for 40 minutes for jook?<br><br>I had the Fish jook with duck egg.  The amount of fish added is generous.  The woman at counter systematically adds cilantro, chopped green onions, delicious fried shallots, and a few drops of some kind of oil.  I added soy sauce, red chili peppers, and a sprinkle of white pepper to my bowl.<br><br>The consistency, flavor, and texture of this jook was out of this world.  A home run and provided justice to the palette for such a long worthwhile wait.<br><br>This is the only hawker stall at Maxwell Food Center with a line.  It is directly in the center of all the stalls.  Note the many certificate of food awards humbly posted here.<br><br>I also recommend the sashimi salad. It&#39;s very similar to ceviche and tastes excellent too.<br><br>For two medium bowls of fish jook and the sashimi salad, it&#39;ll cost you $S10.<br><br>So far, my single best food experience in my brief stay here in Singapore.<br><br>As this place opens at 5:30am, I wouldn&#39;t be surprised if people camp the night before to get this porridge greatness.",
