"reviewcomment":"1. cheese toasties <br>- poached eggs &amp; marmite <br>- the poach egges were perfect! the soughdough was awesome too! toasted to perfection. <br>- the cheese (not sure what type they used) were unfortunately it was way too salty for me :( <br><br>2. turkish eggs<br>- 2 poach eggs with whipped yogurt &amp; hot chili butter served with soughdough<br>- interesting dish but probably would not order again. it tasted like a spicy sour cream dip with poached eggs. interesting, edible but not my favorite thing. (even though the staff recommend this. hm.) maybe I am not a turkish breakfast person. just a simple american breakfast person. <br><br>3. cafe latte (7 ounce, double shot) <br>- strong! <br>- we initially asked for an extra shot because the staff told us 7 ounce will be &#34;diluted with milk&#34; and we wanted to start the day with a good coffee. I guess 2 shot was overkill? the kind of bitter only diehard coffee lovers can love. I am more a mainstream coffee person. <br><br>4. smore tart <br>- THE BEST!!! seriously, based on this item alone the place is worth a visit. the chocolate melts in your mouth! <br><br>Total: $27<br><br>Ambiance: nice vintage coffee joint :) great selection of magazines and books to read too (which is the perfect place to catchup on some reading on a lazy afternoon or during the late evenings when there aren&#39;t too many people. mornings tend to get crowded.) <br><br>Cons: <br>(which could have, but did not, make me give them 3 star. i believe in this place!!! it&#39;s definitely a raising start despite a few initial shortcomings... :) <br>- cash payment only. <br>- limited selection of brunch food (basically toast and eggs? both of which they do very well but I need something more substantial to start the day) I heard they are working on more dishes soon? can&#39;t wait to see what&#39;s installed. if it&#39;s anything like their perfect poached eggs and sourdough toast then it could potentially be a 5 star joint!",
