"reviewcomment":"at first glance, jin jin is indistinguishable from the typical dessert stalls at your neighborhood hawker center, running the gamut of syrupy crushed ice dessert combos.  however at 9.30pm, there was a line, which wasn&#39;t so typical. would probably hate to be here at lunch/dinnertime.   <br><br>anyway, the gangster ice ($2.50) was incredible! think mountain of soft, pillowy crushed ice paired with sour mangoes and sweet durian ice cream (read: rich, luscious durian flesh). also tried the famed power chendol ($1.50) but wasn&#39;t blown away. however i&#39;ve never really liked chendol and didn&#39;t hate this iteration, so that&#39;s probably saying something. thought the gula melaka was sticky and delicious but found the ice a little too chunky. my companion thought it was great so i doubt any chendol fans would be disappointed. <br><br>it&#39;s right around the corner from ikea so think of it as the perfect nightcap to a long night of austere, nordic furniture shopping.",
