"reviewcomment":"Cookie jars lined up on the shopfront and the smell of butter, chocolate chips and nuts wafting from the oven make it impossible to ignore this quaint little bake shop. The Wooden Spoon is decorated like an old country style kitchen with cute lamp shades, checkered cloths and a little red brick wall.<br><br>Oatmeal, chocolate chip, almond butter cookies, and many other varieties that stretch beyond my non-baking vocabulary, come in bite sizes, and they are absolutely delightful (even for a non-sweet tooth like yours truly), for gifting or to polish off all by yourself. Really great tasting cookies that aren&#39;t too sweet, so share them maybe.<br><br>Oh and the awesome lady boss makes muffins, scones and brownies too.",
