"reviewcomment":"After reading positive reviews about the cupcakes from Lamb Cupcakery, I was keen to try some. The first visit was on a Sunday and it was closed (Sunday is their day off). <br><br>Next visit was on a Saturday afternoon and yay! It was open. But....not many cupcakes were left. Once the cupcakes are gone, they will close shop. How nice. It also means all the cupcakes are baked fresh daily.<br><br>I decided to try the Dark Chocolate since Triple Chocolate was already sold out when I got there at 3+pm. It was pretty good, especially if you are a chocolate lover. The frosting was generous with a thick layer of butter cream. The cake itself was like a cake - dense and moist with bits of melted chocolate inside. <br><br>I tried a bit of the Strawberry Chocolate frosting which my friend bought. That was a bit too buttery for me. The cake base was the same as the Dark Chocolate. <br><br>I would definitely return in future to try the other flavors.",
