"reviewcomment":"Went looking for a place called Ganges at #3, as it was recommended in Lonely Planet. It is not there anymore, looks like the neighbours Koala took them over.<br><br>Figuring it was worth a try, the outside menu looked reasonable, so I popped in. It was a Sunday around 2pm, and not too packed - always a good thing.<br><br>The menu looks good, a lot of variety in the veg and non-veg selection. I decided to go for the mutton kulambu set for $7 (according to Google that means curry or gravy). Out comes a massive tray reminiscent of an airline meal with everything in neat sections. There was the mutton curry (very good but small portions), white rice, two sets of veg curry, beans, a papadam, yoghurt, a dessert and a couple more small random dishes.<br><br>Overall this was great, as I said, I would have preferred more of the mutton, but I left full anyhow. The staff saw I was sweating up a storm, so kindly provided more napkins. Thanks.",
