"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WCJw351tldWXzDkmJL-ILw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"When I heard Laduree&#39;s opened in Singapore, I was like &#34;YAYYYYY...&#34; then I realised... Oh crap, that means the whole damn country is going to populate this place. True enough, the entire blogosphere started talking about the long queues and all that. <br><br>And I thought &#34;Meh... I already tried Laduree&#39;s in London anyway...&#34; <br><br>Then the boyfriend showed up one night after my dance class with a bag of macaroons. <br><br>I squealed with joy, then I wondered what the hell he did that he felt he had to surprise me with a bag of macaroons. But that&#39;s besides the point, I got a bag of macaroons!<br><br>Four. To be exact. <br><br>I ate the gold chocolate one first. Seriously, at $7 a piece.. it&#39;s like... just chocolate with gold dust. That&#39;s it. <br><br>The salted caramel was how I remembered it when I ate it in the sweltering London Summer heat. So was the other chocolate one and the lemon one. <br><br>I have tried Pierre Hermes&#39;s macaroons lovingly flown in from Paris by my stewardess bestie.. but it shrunk due to the air pressure, so I couldn&#39;t judge if it&#39;s the best in the world.. yet... <br><br>So until I fulfill my dream of eating BOTH Pierre Hermes&#39;s and Laduree&#39;s macaroons both at the same time...... I&#39;ll say Laduree&#39;s macaroons will be the best &#39;authentic&#39; Parisian macaroon in Singapore for now.",
