"reviewcomment":"I walked past this store a couple of time, always thinking they were only selling authentic chinese products like dried mushrooms, specialty noodles etc. <br>I can&#39;t be blamed because the storefront is just an orange wall. No windows displaying baking products or anything. But don&#39;t be misled by the storefront or signage, this place sells baking products! <br>Not just a few baking products like shermay&#39;s cooking school down the street, but this place sells all baking products you never knew existed. My friend has her own bakery and she says she always go shopping here because they have everything, the quality is superb and the price reasonable to cheap. (except if you want to order something like a kg of almond paste ofcourse). <br>Once you are inside the maze of shells full of baking products is pretty overwhelming, but just tell the staff what you are looking for and they will point you in the right direction. <br>Unexpected tip is to buy cheese here, a kg of mozarella and gouda only costs around 20 sing!",
