"reviewcomment":"While I was staying at the hotel, I came down for breakfast for 2 days, and was very impressed with their spread. They&#39;ve got quite a good selection for breakfast - brunch and they put quite a lot of detail in their presentation, service and product and it&#39;s definitely commendable.<br><br>What I Love: For their breakfast buffet, I sampled and tried everything. What was really cool is that they have a Fresh Fruits and Juice section - and they will make any type of juice you want - and you can choose your own fruits, combine, etc. There are fresh fruits and preserved ones. There is quite a selection for cakes, bread, muffins, etc. My other fave part is the salad and cereal counter - pretty comprehensive, in terms of healthy salad, and cereal options. There&#39;s quite a few milk options too.<br><br>Their omelet section has someone attending to everyone&#39;s orders - and there is the usual bacon, hash and vegetables. There&#39;s also local Singaporean stuff and Dim Sum.<br><br>What I Don&#39;t Love: Nothing! This place is great!",
