"reviewcomment":"It goes without saying, if you want to eat organic in Singapore, it&#39;ll cost you. However, this place is CHEAPER than Supernature just a few blocks down and has just as wide a selection of organic food and household products. I think where Supernature fails, BRP takes over. The store itself isn&#39;t exactly quaint per-se, but hey, it makes up for it with the products and the range of products they carry. They don&#39;t carry a wide selection of multivitamins and fresh/frozen produce, so that&#39;s where Supernature comes in. The selection of dry food is definitely better here, so I&#39;ll be coming to shop here more often for that. <br><br>Oh yea, THEY HAVE ZICO!! The Thai coconut water made easy. I haven&#39;t checked the price on that, but I can assume it won&#39;t be as cheap as I bought it back home in nyc for US$3 a carton.",
