"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/-KpEgEen1tj-jdjIS7uVOw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This is a nice café with a very inviting décor located in Market Street. However, to be honest, it is a little hard to find this place even though it is right in the middle of Raffles Place. It&#39;s behind the M1 shop at Caltex House.<br>Dimbulah prides itself on bringing fine Australian coffee from the plantation straight to the consumer, and it shows: the coffee here is simply mindblowing. <br>They have a breakfast menu as well as a lunch menu. They also have cakes, tarts and muffins on display. However, it seems that most people were there for the coffee.<br>My friend had a triple deck roast chicken sandwich and a chicken pie. The chicken sandwich was nothing special, just three slices of wholemeal sandwich bread with roast chicken and the usual garnishing. The chicken pie was not bad. I had a tuna baguette which was also very normal, so food-wise, it&#39;s really not impressive. As I&#39;ve mentioned though, the  coffee was really good. It&#39;s not harsh and too acidic, and there is kind of an underlying richness which gives the coffee texture and body. Overall, this is a great place to chill. Recommended!",
