"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"My friends and I were looking for a space to sit and chat and have some sweet dessert after our less than satisfying and overly salty dinner, and we decided to check out this gelato place in Marina Square. <br><br>We were deciding between Gelato and Anderson&#39;s Ice cream initially, but saw their board which showed the fat content of gelato vs. ice cream, and decided that gelato seemed like a much healthier choice.<br><br>We sampled a couple of flavors, and ended up picking pistachio, yuzu with milk, and another chocolate one (I forgot the name.. I think it is Bario or Bachio or something).<br><br>The Yuzu with milk is pretty sour on its own (a little more sorbet-ish), but goes very well if you eat it together with the other two flavours which are creamier and stronger. I love love love the pistachio flavor which seems to be quite an acquired taste.<br><br>Will definitely be back here again! Also, limited seating but we were lucky since it was a quiet Monday night. I would think that this place will be pretty crowded on weekends!",
