"reviewcomment":"I&#39;m a bit confused about the name of this restaurant, because all the signs outside the restaurant seem to say &#34;Sun Japanese Dining&#34; but their listing on the official Chijmes website is &#34;Japanese Dining Sun&#34;. Clarification on this would be useful! :)<br><br>Regardless, &#34;Sun&#34; is a fancy sushi restaurant on the second floor of Chijmes. It&#39;s located near Senor Taco, and it shares the second floor with a Korean restaurant. <br><br>When you walk in, you wonder if you&#39;ve stumbled into the middle of a Suntory Whisky commercial, as there&#39;s a lot of Suntory signage near the entrance, around the restaurant, and on the dining tables. You also walk by this beautiful glass casing with all of these whiskies and alcohols, which all look promising.<br><br>Their menu is pretty extensive. Sushi and sashimi are quite pricy, but the quality is top notch. I enjoyed my sushi set, and the chef even surprised me by deep frying the prawn heads from my prawn sushi. It was surprisingly delicious! (Then again, tell me something deep fried that isn&#39;t delicious.)  My husband wasn&#39;t too hungry so he opted for their mini rice bowl with sashimi on top. It was $25 and REALLY mini! He also ordered tempura veggies, which we liked and highly recommend. <br><br>The service was very good. We came on a Saturday evening, and although they were a little busy, our orders came out very quickly and we weren&#39;t left waiting too long. Overall, a good choice for date night or for business. Next time I stop by, I&#39;ll be sure to explore their whisky offerings!",
