"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/kIJ8sLaGBpqaErmL4DAjPw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I had iftar with a view of the sea. When the waiters learnt that I was fasting this Ramadan, they handed me and my Chinese friend complimentary glasses of rose syrup water, sliced oranges and dates to start my iftar.<br><br>Ooh, we felt so spoilt at this restaurant. It had  a classy ambience and a menu of Persian and Indian food. The waiter patiently explained to us what the Persian items contained when we couldn&#39;t make them out. My only gripe is that a few items I wanted to try isn&#39;t available anymore. We ended up sharing shawarma, chicken shish kebab and gulab jamun. The food was excellent - the kebab came with big juicy, tender chicken chunks and the shawarma was delectable. The gulab jamun wasn&#39;t as sweet as the waiter said.<br><br>I could go on and on and on about the service. They were quite a number of other diners, but  the restaurant didn&#39;t compromise on service. When our order came, the manager and waiters cared enough to ask if it tasted good. And they made sure our glasses were never empty. They gave in to our requests for extra cutlery as we wanted to share the food. <br><br>And you know what the best part was? We spent just $40 for our meal near the sea.",
