"reviewcomment":"Fantastic food at an affordable price point. Fatien Bar a Vin serves typical bistro food to be paired with a myriad of wines, many of which are offered by the glass. From their house Fatien label in Burgundy, I had several delicious wines notably a Beaune which was fruity and full of cherries. <br>the food was excellent cooking indeed - rillette of three kinds with crusty bread - salmon, pork and duck- a generous portion for SGD 18. The onglet beef, my main course, was fabulous. Very flavourful and tender beef well seasoned , accompanied by the most authentic and rough cut pommes frites, and a shallot confit of caramelized shallots. Dessert was a apple tarte tatin which was excellent in execution- caramelized and with a nice crisp texture in the puff pastry. Overall very highly recommended - especially considering the pricings.",
