"reviewcomment":"We reserved a table for 2 during restaurant week, not knowing what to expect. It was a pleasant surprise that the ambience here was so refreshing and inviting. With the ingenious &#34;hexagonal&#34; motifs, along with their cosy chairs, this is a perfect place to spend the afternoon, just savouring the food and chilling to the soothing background music. The staff are attentive, and extremely pleasant. <br><br>The food was definitely worth the price. The restaurant week menu comprised of lobster bisque for starters, beef ragout for mains ($35) and the nutella chocolate tart ($14) for dessert. The lobster bisque was most delightful, and lucky for me, I managed to get the last serving before they ran out. It just goes to show how popular that dish was. The beef was nicely done, and well complemented by the sauteed vegetables and mashed potatoes. Ah, the dessert was simply heavenly, with bursts of bitter chocolate, perfectly combined with that sweet hazelnut chocolate. <br><br>Definitely a place I will return to, especially since one can always pop over for drinks at the bar at Scarlet Hotel (where Our Korner is housed), or simply go for a post-meal stroll along the idyllic Ann Siang Road district which has many quirky stores.",
