"reviewcomment":"Great, great desserts and a yummy place to get local and Indonesian specialities. Growing up with all the traditional Kueh - it&#39;s always nice to walk by and just grab a few - even if it&#39;s just one or 2 pieces. From Ondeh-Ondeh to modern cream cakes - this chain offers quite a selection.<br><br>What I Love: My fave ones are the traditional options - from Ondeh-Ondeh, Talam Ubi, Kueh Salat, Dodol, Kueh Bugis, Corn Kueh, Kueh Jongkong, Sago Melaka  to Pulut Inti - it&#39;s really a plethora of flavors. If you want something less traditional, you could get the famous Pandan Sponge Cake, Swissroll and a few other cakes. Prices are affordable - and they&#39;ll pack it really nicely for you - depending on whether you&#39;re taking some overseas or for a party. I brought quite a bit of Kueh to Australia - and they were totally fine!<br><br>What I Don&#39;t Love: The good ones or certain types finish pretty early - so good to buy in bulk or get down earlier in the day.",
