"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Dropped by the Riverwalk area to renew EP/DP. <br><br>We came a bit early and noticed Riverwalk Tandoor so we dropped in for a quick bite. We knew it&#39;d be quick b/c it was a buffet style lunch for $16++.<br><br>Came in with zero expectations but was pleasantly surprised by the food. I believe it&#39;s more North Indian fare but man, everything was delicious and well prepared. They did not skimp on the quality of the food. Ingredients tasted fresh and each dish carefully prepared.<br><br>When you sit down they take your drink order (additional charge) and bring you a basket of the chewiest, warm, buttery plain naan ever. I could have filled up on them bad boys. I believe the naan is also free flow although one basket was more than enough for us.<br><br>Highlights include the saffron rice, tandoori chicken, aloo gobi, daal, hmm I&#39;m just listing everything I had.<br><br>They also have a nice dessert section with fresh fruit and galub jamun. This was some good gj - not overpoweringly sweet, just warm enough and the right sponginess.<br><br>The place was not busy when we came and the service was very attentive - removing used plates and refilling our drinks.<br><br>Can&#39;t wait to find another excuse to come back to Riverwalk Tandoor!",
