"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Kids, this is a 4* when I tell people about it but a 5* for myself.<br><br>Things are simple here but consistent. I love the hideaway on the 2nd floor vibe. wood, art and comic panels tables. <br><br>You wouldn&#39;t ever call this slick. Instead the coffee is reliable and full-bodied, I&#39;ve actually had it several times before I cut this review. A good sized cup latte for $5. Skinny and fat what have you. They are very new and plan to add to the food options. But along this stretch there&#39;s a dearth of reliable coffee since Homebodies closed down next door. They do soy but they have a bit of problems getting a consistent supply. Talked to the barista and their preference is for soy to taste like soy and not one of those which is so clean tasting it could be milk. When they do have it, it makes a tasty drink and I feel like I&#39;m taking care of myself ;)<br><br>This is the daytime visage of the Spiffy Dapper. Madi is the barista behind the Rancilio. He was last at Chye Seng Huat, but I&#39;ll say the coffee I&#39;ve had here is more consistent than at CSH.<br><br>I&#39;ve had the sous vide eggs. They were perfectly done. Very wholesome...ask for worcestershire and hot sauce with yours (that&#39;s how I take mine). The ciabatta is tasty and the kaya has a nice caramel flavour to it, it&#39;s not just pure sugar like some places. I love sitting at the bar looking at the various bottles of gin on display :D<br><br>Menu is currently a very short list but I keep finding reasons to come back.",
