"reviewcomment":"I used to be a fan of Crystal Jade char siew bo luo bao which is available at most outlets around Singapore. The standard is not consistent and sometimes it&#39;s really soggy. The search for quality bo luo bao ended at Imperial Treasures Bakery, which i stumbled upon at Triple One. This is like hitting the Bo Luo Bao jackpot. It&#39;s awesome when it&#39;s out fresh, crispy and crumbly bo luo top which has sugar granules in it. Then you split open that soft pillowy bun to taste that nice caramelized honey pork (done the Cantonese style). This texture has not been found in dimsum joints in Singapore yet. <br><br>The egg tart is also to die for and they taste as awesome even if you leave them overnight. Of course it&#39;s better fresh. The buttery shortcrust pastry crumbles and melts in your mouth while the wobbly egg custard is almost slurpable. It&#39;s a definite must try. <br><br>I believe this is the only bakery by Imperial Treasures but I&#39;m glad it is still staying that way so as to maintain the quality of the buns. Yums.",
