"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WKWsUPsCtoylGyywP7cT1A/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I was at Ogopogo last night and at first I found the name a bit of a mouthful to pronounce but all these were set aside after the staff at the cafe greeted me with a big cheery &#34;HELLO!&#34; <br><br>The ambiance of the place was quite 1970-80 ish. People like me who were born during that era will find it a fair bit nostalgic with their quirky chairs and toys on display.. they have those 10 cents lollipops I used to buy in Primary School sold straight from the jar. <br><br>Their menu which arrived in the form of a jotterbook, which according to the staff, each and every book was painstakingly handwritten (so don&#39;t go spilling drinks or food on the jotterbook since it was someone&#39;s blood, sweat and tears!). They have coffee, lattes, beers, ciders, sodas and smoothies. They also have a range of cakes available and a little shisha place at the back where unlike other places, you don&#39;t have to smoking by the street side with the cars zooming by and people staring at you. It&#39;s a nice private enclosed open space at the back where other than the distant sounds from the other stores around Ogopogo, you can pretty much smoke in peace. <br><br>If you are hungry, feel free to ask the owners for their food menu. They have an arabian food menu and an italian menu where once you order, the staff will run to the stores next door and place your order for you. <br><br>I really like the ambiance of this place as it&#39;s very laidback, the staff are very friendly and the drinks are delicious! Will definitely come back for more here!",
