"reviewcomment":"You need meat, and they got meat. Slabs and slabs and slabs - frozen up front in easy takeaway packs for that last-minute steamboat sesh, or juicy sirloins in the chiller in case you were thinking of a steak dinner.<br><br>The fact that they sit on the ground floor of Changi City Point doesn&#39;t hurt either! I&#39;m digging the fact that the store isn&#39;t far form where I live, and the almost wholesale prices are really hard to beat, especially when you look around, and the only other place you might find a decent cut of meat at is Cold Storage... and I&#39;m not paying retail, thanks.<br><br>I got six almost-300g pieces of Angus Striploin cut for me from the mother massive slab (probably upwards of 5kgs), and it only cost me just over $60 for the lot. You can ask for seasoning on site if you want, and the mixed herb is pretty good!<br><br>They&#39;ve got another store on the fourth floor of Square 2 in Novena, and the warehouse (yes, I&#39;ve been there too) in Jurong, where they&#39;ve got a massive selection, including a homemade samabal.",
