"reviewcomment":"The famous carrot cake at Chomp Chomp Hawker Centre is popular for its oyster omelette and white carrot cake.<br><br>What makes this dish, consisting of just egg, kueh, chye poh and spring onions so special is that the stall has mashed up the kueh thoroughly, which allows the sauces to soak in. <br><br>They also use the sweet type of chye poh, which is slightly more expensive than the standard salty ones. With all the extra effort in preparation and ingredients and strong wok fire, chomp chomp store 36 carrot cake is crispy on the outside, mashy with bits of sweet chye poh, egg and spring onion makes it one one of the best chye tao kueh I&#39;ve ever tasted!",
