"reviewcomment":"We stopped here to eat dinner for the same reason as a previous reviewer did. The line at Long Phung was longer than my patience would have been. Betel Box was Plan B and we loved it. The place is very cool to browse after you have ordered.  The gents bathroom has a fantastic mural on the wall and the library of books make interesting reading. Oh, and the food is great. Beef Rendang, spicy wing beans and a fruity pork dish whose name escapes us unfortunately. <br><br>Service was quick and friendly.  In fact service, so often the downfall of SG restaurants was as good as it gets. <br><br>The food was washed down with some great cider from the UK and with some coffee to finish, we were on our way through the great night time people watching area of Joo Chiat. Would definitely come back.",
