"reviewcomment":"Was around Upper Thomas road and decided to have some dessert after dinner. There were like 3-4 ice cream stall around the area and we chose Salted Caramel.<br><br>Entering the shop, we were greeted by the service crew straight away. We went straight to choose the ice cream we want. I tried the Avocado flavor and it was very true, like eating the real fruit. Furthermore, the ice cream are milky and melt slower. So it really taste like eating the fruit and not ice cream.<br><br>Finally, we choose two flavors, the specialty, salted caramel and another flavor, Earl Grey. The salted caramel is really nice but what shocked me was the Earl Grey flavor. The first time I tried an Earl Grey ice cream and I would really want to introduce to everyone! It was great! It does not have the bitten taste of tea but the fragrant smell of tea plus a little lemon taste.<br><br>I will definitely go back again for the Earl Grey Ice cream. Definitely!",
