"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Two words: default dessert. They aren&#39;t everywhere yet, so when I do see them in the mall, I go a little nuts.<br>I&#39;ve probably been to this branch more times than I can remember - and the one thing you HAVE to try is the black ball signature. Grass jelly over their special shaved ice, topped with sweet red beans, bubble tea pearls, and what can best be described as gnocchi... made of sweet potato and yam. Pretty phenomenal.<br>What&#39;s so special? That grass jelly has a stretchier consistency, which gives it a little more bite (yes, I know I&#39;m fine-dining-describing grass jelly), and that shaved ice isn&#39;t ordinary ice - it&#39;s ice made from grass jelly water, so your dessert is never watered down. Fun fact: I discovered only YESTERDAY that you can also get winter melon tea shaved ice. It blew my mind. Seriously.",
