"reviewcomment":"Before and after the renovation, this branch of Cold Storage was, is, and probably always will be my favourite branch.<br><br>There&#39;s a spectacular cheese selection, decent deli choices, plenty of vegetables and fresh herbs, including a organic veggies section, and many many many frozen foods.<br><br>There&#39;s just a good solid range of pantry filling foods to be found here, and it&#39;s my go-to place for aimless grocery shopping. I always find something.<br><br>To be fair, Fairprice IS cheaper, especially for vegetables, so if you have a quick need, that&#39;s usually cheaper, but for good looking veggies, harder to find stuff like different kinds of creme (double, thickened, whipping, fraiche, clotted), buttermilk, rice milk, hazelnut milk, you&#39;ll find all of that here.<br><br>Maybe it isn&#39;t such a great place if you&#39;re lactose intolerant, now that I reread what I&#39;ve wrote, but still. I love this branch deeply. If only they were 24h!",
