"reviewcomment":"Well well, what can I say about this favourite supper place of mine? This is the best fishball noodles that I had. A regular bowl of noodles costs $3.50 and has three fishballs, one tau pok filled with fish paste and one fish dumpling. To add one more of everything (aka jia1 liao4), it will cost $5. I feel the serving size for $3.50 is kinda small. <br><br>After ordering, you will be given a number. You can choose to stand around awkwardly watching others savouring their noodles. Or you can go to the corner Muslim coffee shop and have a sup kambing (at least that&#39;s what I did. Lol.)<br><br>Do expect:<br>- Soft and bouncy fishballs<br>- Pork lard spammed springy mee pok (even better with chilli)<br>- Fish dumplings that are amazingly delicious<br>- A bowl of soup that is there for the sake of being there. <br>- Up to an hour of waiting time<br><br>My friends and I always head there around 9 odd at night for supper and the place is packed. But since I really like their noodles, I find 30-45 mins of waiting time still okay.",
