"reviewcomment":"Cedele&#39;s has always been one of my favourite places to dine, be it a brunch or dinner. They have a great selection of food, from all day breakfast to pasta to burgers to cakes which all come with one promise - healthy food that tastes good.<br><br>I frequent this particular Cedele&#39;s a lot, as there is usually no need to queue to get a seat for two people. My favourites here are the Rose&#39;s Laksa Pasta which is a chicken curry-eqsue pasta that comes with tender bits of chicken and tastes like rendang, and also the Fish Pesto Garlic Pasta that comes with a huge serving of fish, with the pesto and garlic really complementing each other very well. The all day breakfast is also good, but the sausage tastes a bit too healthy for my liking.<br><br>If you&#39;re looking for something light, go for the soup and bread bar where you can just order one soup and get free flow bread (self service, of course). They have such a variety of bread that you&#39;ll definitely find something you like.<br><br>And for dessert, Cedele has an awesome range of cakes to choose from. My favourites are the carrot walnut cake and the chocolate truffle cake. The first is a hearty, creamy cake while the second has a rich, chocolatey taste.<br><br>I don&#39;t think you can really go wrong with Cedele&#39;s, and furthermore their prices are really decent seeing that they don&#39;t add on for GST and service charge.",
